commit.message:
DOC: README.rst: note about pytest support

- https://stackoverflow.com/questions/39162569/use-ipdb-instead-of-pdb-with-py-test-pdb-option
- https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/reference/customize.html

Fix CI badge

Replace broken Travis CI badge with a GitHub Actions one.

Use context manager for opening toml config file

Use context manager for file opening, will close file properly once work is finished.  Will resolve ResourceWarnings in unittests

Update tests.yml

Add separate tests for 3.11+, refactor hasattr call to call proper 3.11+ Pdb attribute.

Move a function call outside local exception handling.

This call to `get_config` can raise exceptions, and it is not correct
to catch any of them locally.
Add a test case for `get_context_from_config` with invalid config.
Extract helper function to set up config files fixture for test cases.

Extract stand-alone helper function `write_lines_to_file`.

The function does not depend on the class or instance, and we will
need it for another TestCase class.

Update dependencies

Patches out vulnerable versions of IPython from CVE-2022-21699.
See more info https://ipython.readthedocs.io/en/stable/whatsnew/version8.html#ipython-8-0-1-cve-2022-21699

Make ipdb work with consolidated Pdb._run()

In Python 3.11, the _runmodule() and _runscript() methods of Pdb were
consolidated into _run(). Specifying the use case is by wrapping the
module or file name in _ModuleTarget or _ScriptTarget, respectively.

Signed-off-by: Nils Philippsen <nils@redhat.com>

Add minimal PEP517 setup

This commit avoids use of the deprecated `setup_requires` to replace the
currently-incorrect use of `install_requires` by setting up a minimal
PEP517 compatible `pyproject.toml`. `install_requires` is for runtime
dependencies while the PEP517 `build-system` stuff is where you specify
what is needed to build or install the project, not what you need to
import the module.
Add support for Python 3.11, remove toml dependency

Remove ppc64le tests

Reverts #208. This was a marketing campaign via PR by IBM. This project is pure python so does not need testing on alternative CPU architectures. And no one reported any problems with ppc64le, because basically no one uses it.

Test on Python 3.10 final

And mark support.
